main event: An unidentified object was observed by a commercial aircraft (Pan America 764, Boeing 707) between Nandi and Australia.
interesting points: The object was observed at an altitude of approximately 35 degrees, traveling from NNE to WSW.
The object's speed was undetermined, but its brightness was comparable to the planet Venus.
The object disappeared at an altitude of approximately 50 degrees, and its intensity did not appear to vary as it traversed the Earth's atmosphere, unlike a meteorite burning up.
The object disappeared behind a cloud deck.
The report was evaluated to be a possible sighting of a U.S. satellite.
sighted object: One unidentified bright object in the sky
